Program: The History Hour
Title: The 43 Group: Battling British Fascists
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csv0wc
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 22 Oct 2017
How Jewish veterans fought fascism in post war Britain; plus investigating the death of Mozambique's president Samora Machel, we hear from a survivor of the Moscow theatre siege, inside the Cuba Missile Crisis and the mystery of Booker prize winner JG Farrell. Photo:British Fascist Sir Oswald Mosley speaking at a rally, Hertford Road, Dalston, London, May 1st 1948. (Getty Images) Show less